11/03/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis says 2005 should be a year of fundamental change and reform.
Addressing the ruling New Democracy party's Political Council on Thursday (10 March), he warned that the country cannot be led by policies from the 1970s.
Karamanlis said he is satisfied with his cabinet's work in the first year of its four-year term.
The New Democracy Central Committee assured him that the party fully supports the reform programme.
(ANA - 10/03/05)
